        <productionVolumeComment xml:lang="en">Production volume is expressed in kg. About 15,531,400 culms of Guadua Angustifolia Kunt were harvested in Ecuador in 2022 on approximately 15,000 ha (INBAR, 2015). 1.67 kg of culm are needed to produce 1 pole and a pole weights about 18 kg (Fabian Moreno, project manager INBAR Ecuador). 31% of harvested bamboo culms are destinated to construction, therefore, this percentage is considered to be used to produce bamboo pole. 
Reference:
INBAINBAR. (2015). Estudio de la cadena desde la producción al consumo del bambú en Ecuador. https://bambuecuador.files.wordpress.com/2018/01/2015-estudio-de-la-cadena-desde-la-producciocc81n-al-consumo-del-bmabucc81-en-ecuador.pdf



</productionVolumeComment>
